     


                                                                  GIT RESPOSITORY AND INITIALIZATION
        

                                

   1> git --version = checks whether git installed and displays the installed git version.



   2> Repository = it is a project folder where git stores and manages the projects history records and version.

                   it managed by Git.



   3> git init = this command coverts a normal folder into a git reposistory and create a hidden .git folder and starts git tracking for the project.



   4> .git folder = .git is hidden folder created by git.
    
                    It stores: project history,versions, git configuration, project records.



   5> git status = this command tells us:

                   i> current branch
                   ii> commit status
                  iii> new files
                   iv> modified files
                   v> reposistory status

   6> How git identifies a project
     
      git first checks whether the current folder contains a .git folder.


        #> if .git exists = git recognizes it as a reposistory.
        #> if .git doesn't exist = git checks the parent folder.
        #> if no .git is found = git shows:  =  fatal: not a git repository


                                        



  
